==Hindi==
===Etymology===
From Old Indo-Aryan ''rasa-''
===Noun===
'''रस''' (ras) {{m}}
# [[sap]], [[juice]], [[gum]]
# [[syrup]]
# a [[liquid]], fluid, water
# [[liquor]]
# [[gravy]], [[soup]], [[broth]]
# (metaphoric) the best or prime part (of anything), [[essence]], marrow, pith
# [[potion]], poisonous drink, [[poison]]
# constituent fluid or essential bodily fluid
# quicksilver, [[mercury]]
# [[taste]], [[savor]], [[flavor]], [[relish]]
# [[pleasure]], [[joy]]
# [[elegance]], [[charm]], [[wit]]

===References===
*McGregor, R.S, ed. ''The Oxford Hindi-English Dictionary'', Oxford university press. 1993
*Platts, John T. ''[http://dsal.uchicago.edu/dictionaries/platts/ A dictionary of Urdu, Classical Hindi, and English]'' Oxford. 1884.

